FL,326,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F325A1783691326
OL,3,CGreek man found guilty of 2009 murder
OL,4,Cof British expat in Crete
OL,6,FAuthorities on the island initially
OL,7,Fruled her death an accidental
OL,8,Fdrowning, but her family suspected
OL,9,Ffoul play and called for the
OL,10,Finvestigation to be reopened.
OL,12,FFollowing years of campaigning, Greek
OL,13,Fauthorities agreed to reopen the case
OL,14,Fin 2024 and arrested a man in his 50s
OL,15,Fthe following year in connection with
OL,16,Fher death.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G2/14
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,326,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F325A1783691326
OL,3,CGreek man found guilty of 2009 murder
OL,4,Cof British expat in Crete
OL,6,FReacting to the verdict outside court,
OL,7,FJean's son Robert Porter said: "I'm
OL,8,Fjust grateful that a room full of
OL,9,Fstrangers just listened to my Mum's
OL,10,Fvoice and came to the right decision."
OL,12,FMichael Porter, also one of Jean's
OL,13,Fsons, said: "(We) really hope that
OL,14,Fthis victory will give other families,
OL,15,Fwho are - and will continue to - go
OL,16,Fthrough this ordeal hope and faith and
OL,17,Fdetermination to just keep pushing."
OL,19,FThe Greek man who has been convicted
OL,20,Fcannot be named under the country's
OL,21,Flaws.
OL,26,@uD@NpmuD@Qpn
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G3/14
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,326,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F325A1783691326
OL,3,CGreek man found guilty of 2009 murder
OL,4,Cof British expat in Crete
OL,6,FThe man, who was known to Jean, was
OL,7,Fcharged with 'murder with intent in a
OL,8,Fcalm mental state' and went on trial
OL,9,Fon 30 June 2026. He repeatedly denied
OL,10,Fcausing her death.
OL,12,FThe court recognised the defendant's
OL,13,Fdiminished responsibility, under
OL,14,FArticle 36 of the Greek criminal code,
OL,15,Fdue to his mental health. This means
OL,16,Fhe will be given a reduced sentence.
OL,18,FDelivering the verdict, the Head Judge
OL,19,Fsaid: "The court declares him
OL,20,Funanimously guilty."
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G4/14
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,326,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F325A1783691326
OL,3,CGreek man found guilty of 2009 murder
OL,4,Cof British expat in Crete
OL,6,FEvidence suggests Jean went to
OL,7,FHeraklion with a man and had drinks at
OL,8,Fa bar near to the harbour on the night
OL,9,Fshe was killed.
OL,11,FText messages sent from her phone to
OL,12,Ffriends implied she did not want to
OL,13,Fstay at the marina with the man but
OL,14,Fdid not indicate she was in fear of
OL,15,Fher life.
OL,17,FShe asked her friends to join them but
OL,18,Fthey failed to respond. One of her
OL,19,Ftext messages read: "Help".
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G5/14
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,326,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F325A1783691326
OL,3,CGreek man found guilty of 2009 murder
OL,4,Cof British expat in Crete
OL,6,FThe Public Prosecutor said in her
OL,7,Fclosing statement that when Jean died
OL,8,Fa "proper investigation" was not
OL,9,Finitially carried out by the
OL,10,Fauthorities.
OL,12,FShe said: "Jean went with a man to the
OL,13,Fmarina cafe, where it appears she was
OL,14,Fnot enjoying herself. She was
OL,15,Fconstantly on the phone and called her
OL,16,Ffriends to make their way there and
OL,17,Fjoin her.
OL,26,@uD@Krr
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G6/14
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,326,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F325A1783691326
OL,3,CGreek man found guilty of 2009 murder
OL,4,Cof British expat in Crete
OL,6,F"The person that has made their way
OL,7,Fwith Jean to Heraklion, from the case
OL,8,Ffile and the evidence provided in the
OL,9,Ftrial, and mostly from the defendant's
OL,10,Ftestimony in front of us, I think it
OL,11,Fis obvious that the man is the accused.
OL,13,F"The defendant having felt rejection
OL,14,Fand seeing her talk to others became
OL,15,Fangry. He stopped taking his
OL,16,Fmedication and for me, he is the only
OL,17,Fone that at the time had any motive to
OL,18,Fdo it."
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G7/14
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,326,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32508
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F325A1783691326
OL,3,CGreek man found guilty of 2009 murder
OL,4,Cof British expat in Crete
OL,6,FThe family lawyer, Apostolos
OL,7,FXiritakis, said in his closing
OL,8,Fargument: "A journal is a mirror of a
OL,9,Fperson's soul."
OL,11,FHe added: "We have one and only one
OL,12,Fperson obsessively following her. In
OL,13,Fher diary we have no mention of anyone
OL,14,Felse.
OL,16,F"In (the defendant's) sister's
OL,17,Ftestimony, she told us that when he
OL,18,Fdoesn't take his medication he becomes
OL,19,Fviolent.
OL,26,@pD@KOUxD@EpmxD@Upn
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G8/14
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,326,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32509
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F325A1783691326
OL,3,CGreek man found guilty of 2009 murder
OL,4,Cof British expat in Crete
OL,6,F"She also said his medication made him
OL,7,Fimpotent, yet he tells us he had
OL,8,Frelations with Jean many times.
OL,10,F"His testimony was full of
OL,11,Fcontradictions. He tried to play down
OL,12,Fthe relationship, saying they knew
OL,13,Feach other for just a few days but
OL,14,Fthat is not true."
OL,16,FIn his closing statement, the
OL,17,Fdefendant's lawyer George Athanatos,
OL,18,Fsaid: "I do not think there is the
OL,19,Fevidence here to lead the court to
OL,20,Fjudge that the defendant murdered her.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G9/14
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,326,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32510
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F325A1783691326
OL,3,CGreek man found guilty of 2009 murder
OL,4,Cof British expat in Crete
OL,6,F"You need to have inductive reasoning
OL,7,Fto say he killed her. So I consider
OL,8,Fthat your court has no cast iron proof
OL,9,Fto convict the defendant."
OL,11,FJean's three sons gave evidence at the
OL,12,Fstart of the trial on Tuesday (30
OL,13,FJune), describing how close they were
OL,14,Fto their mother.
OL,16,FThey also referred to a diary their
OL,17,Fmum kept, in which the accused was
OL,18,Fnamed.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G10/14
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,326,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32511
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F325A1783691326
OL,3,CGreek man found guilty of 2009 murder
OL,4,Cof British expat in Crete
OL,6,FIn it, Jean claims the man would not
OL,7,Fleave her alone and would continually
OL,8,Fpursue a relationship she did not wish
OL,9,Fto continue.
OL,11,FThe defendant's sister took to the
OL,12,Fstand on Wednesday (1 July) and spoke
OL,13,Fabout his poor mental health.
OL,15,FShe said he had been prescribed
OL,16,Fmedication from a young age and said
OL,17,Fif he didn't take it, he would "become
OL,18,Faggressive" and would have "no memory
OL,19,Fof his actions".
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G11/14
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,326,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32512
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F325A1783691326
OL,3,CGreek man found guilty of 2009 murder
OL,4,Cof British expat in Crete
OL,6,FThroughout the trial the defendant has
OL,7,Fdenied any involvement in Jean's death
OL,8,Fand, when asked about his relationship
OL,9,Fwith her, he said they had only met a
OL,10,Fhandful of times.
OL,12,FHowever, when the judge referred to
OL,13,FJean's diary, which contained entries
OL,14,Fsuggesting they had known each other
OL,15,Ffor several months, he accepted those
OL,16,Fdiary entries were referring to him.
OL,18,FSince Jean's death, her family have
OL,19,Fmaintained the belief that the
OL,20,Fevidence did not to point to an
OL,21,Faccident.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G12/14
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,326,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32513
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F325A1783691326
OL,3,CGreek man found guilty of 2009 murder
OL,4,Cof British expat in Crete
OL,6,FHer three son's argued that injuries
OL,7,Fsustained by Jean before her death
OL,8,Fwarranted further examination and that
OL,9,Fimportant questions remained about her
OL,10,Ffinal hours.
OL,12,FFor nearly 20 years the family
OL,13,Ftravelled repeatedly to Greece, hired
OL,14,Fa private investigator and sought
OL,15,Findependent reviews of the evidence.
OL,17,FFresh analysis was carried out,
OL,18,Fincluding looking at Jean's personal
OL,19,Fdiary, re-examining the findings of
OL,20,Fthe autopsy and revising witness
OL,21,Ftestimonies.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G13/14
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
